text: The men's trap (originally called clay bird shooting) was a shooting sports event held as part of the shooting at the 1912 Summer Olympics programme. It was the third appearance of the event, which had been introduced in 1900. The competition was held from Tuesday, 2 July 1912 to Thursday, 4 July 1912. Sixty-one sport shooters from eleven nations competed. ==Results== {| class=wikitable style="text-align:center" |- !
